HEADWORD: Azotite
<hw>Az"o*tite</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A salt formed by the combination of azotous, or nitrous, acid with
a base; a nitrite.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

